---
import omni from "@assets/omni.webp";
import MainLayout from "@layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<MainLayout>
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Projects I've Worked On</h2>
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="flex flex-col space-y-4 md:flex-row md:space-x-6 md:space-y-0">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0">
        <Image
          alt="Project 1 screenshot"
          class="h-48 w-full rounded-md object-cover shadow-md md:w-64"
          src={omni}
        />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col space-y-4">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">Omni Lawns</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          <p>
            Omni Lawns was designed to establish an online presence in the <span
              class="font-semibold text-blue-600"
              >lawn care service industry</span
            >. ImplementingÂ a <span class="italic text-gray-900">modern UI</span
            >
            helped to engage with customers and increase conversions by <span
              class="font-bold text-green-600">30%</span
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            I collaborated closely with the owner, Tiago, to understand his
            needs and the message he wanted to send to his customers. As this
            was Tiago's first business, and he was doing it to help his family
            succeed in the future, his message would resonate with potential
            clients.
          </p>
          <p>
            A key learning experience was diving deeper into the innards of the <span
              class="underline decoration-gray-500">Astro</span
            >
            and <span class="underline decoration-gray-500">Tailwind</span> frameworks
            to provide a streamlined and modern workflow.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="https://example.com/project1"
          class="inline-block font-medium text-blue-600 hover:underline"
          target="_blank"
        >
          View Project &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
